---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Analytics & Dashboard Services"
  description="Business intelligence dashboards that people actually use. Real-time KPIs, single source of truth, answers in seconds for UK SMEs."
>
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate">Analytics & Dashboards</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-slate-light">
        A dashboard that everyone trusts. KPIs that actually matter. Answers in seconds, not hours. We build business intelligence that fits how you work.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-light">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate">The Problem</h2>
        <p>
          Most dashboard projects fail. Not because the technology is wrong, but because:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Data comes from multiple systems that don't agree</li>
          <li>Nobody trusts the numbers, so they check manually anyway</li>
          <li>The dashboard shows everything but answers nothing</li>
          <li>It was designed for software demos, not your actual decisions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate mt-12">What We Build</h2>
        <div class="not-prose grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate">Executive Dashboards</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-light text-sm">High-level KPIs that answer "how are we doing?" at a glance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate">Operations Dashboards</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-light text-sm">Real-time visibility into what's happening now—and what needs attention.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate">Sales & Marketing Analytics</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-light text-sm">Pipeline visibility, conversion tracking, and campaign performance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate">Financial Reporting</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-light text-sm">Automated financial dashboards that replace manual board pack preparation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate mt-12">Our Approach</h2>
        <p>
          We start with the decisions you need to make, then work backwards to the data. The result is dashboards that:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Answer real questions</strong>—not just display metrics</li>
          <li><strong>Use a single source of truth</strong>—no more conflicting numbers</li>
          <li><strong>Update automatically</strong>—no manual refresh required</li>
          <li><strong>Get adopted</strong>—because they're designed around your workflow</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate mt-12">Technology</h2>
        <p>
          We build dashboards in tools your team can maintain: Power BI, Tableau, Looker, or custom web applications where needed. We're agnostic to platforms—we recommend what fits your situation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    title="Ready for dashboards that work?"
    description="Book a discovery call to discuss your reporting challenges."
  />
</BaseLayout>
